The paper deals with approximation algorithms for estimating the free energy of Ising models, which is a problem in statistical physics. However, the paper also uses techniques from theoretical computer science, such as convex relaxations and the Sherali-Adams hierarchy. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are all possible sub-categories that this paper could belong to.
